<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-3231]  Purge task may lost data when the recent snapshots are all invalid</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-3231</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&#160;read the ZooKeeper source code, and I find the purge task use&#160;FileTxnSnapLog#findNRecentSnapshots to find snapshots, but the method does not check whether the snapshots are valid.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Consider a worse case, a ZooKeeper server may have many invalid snapshots, and when a purge task begins, it will use the zxid in the last snapshot&apos;s name to purge old snapshots and transaction logs, then we may lost data.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we should use&#160;FileSnap#findNValidSnapshots(int)&#160;instead of FileSnap#findNRecentSnapshots in&#160;FileTxnSnapLog#findNRecentSnapshots, but I am not sure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
