                            <comment id="16736548" author="nixon" created="Tue, 8 Jan 2019 01:15:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It might also make sense to more aggressively delete invalid snapshots (in the mode of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-3082&quot; title=&quot;Fix server snapshot behavior when out of disk space&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;ZOOKEEPER-3082&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;ZOOKEEPER-3082&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). If its straightforward to identify and purge such files then we won&apos;t have to worry about deleting valid snapshots in order to preserve invalid snapshots.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16737076" author="maoling" created="Tue, 8 Jan 2019 12:23:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jiangjiafu&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jiangjiafu&quot;&gt;jiangjiafu&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;good issue.yep!&lt;br/&gt;
the data-loss situation can only happen when the retained count of snapshots were all invalid(very unfortunately&#65292;little probability) and at that time,zk server took any new snapshots.&lt;br/&gt;
the specific source codes about the &lt;b&gt;restore&lt;/b&gt; can be found in:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
FileTxnSnapLog#restore---&amp;gt;snapLog.deserialize&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
